how ben sets up his i3 WM :)


install Gentoo -


emerge -av xorg-x11 xorg-drivers xterm xclock xterm twm xinit networkmanager nm-applet volumeicon pulseaudio alsa-lib alsa-utils alsa-plugins pavucontrol bluez bluez-firmware xfce4-terminamm

install i3 file manager menu --

emerge -av i3 i3 status dmenu thunar thunar-archive-plugin thunar-media-tags-plugin thunar-volman
​
install archive management

emerge engrampa xarchiver unrar p7zip zip
​
install apps 

emerge -av google-chrome cmus clementine spotify teamviewer firefox-bin rxvt-unicode zsh compton lxapperance

git clone and setup i3 and zsh

git clone https://github.com/bfitzgit23/i3-config.git

copy i3 config file and i3status config to /home/user/.config/i3 and /home/user/.config/i3status

copy compton config to /home/user/.config/ or /home/user/.config/compton

setup zsh

grab ohmyzsh from http://ohmyz.sh/ using commands from website and set agnoster zsh theme in ~/.zshrc

grab powerline fonts from https://github.com/powerline/fonts and in terminal run - cd fonts and do sudo ./install.sh

use flags for packages -

x11-terms/rxvt-unicode 256-color blink fading-colors iso14755 pixbuf unicode3 xft
www-client/w3m imlib
media-sound/cmus cddb wma zsh-completion
gnome-base/gvfs afp archive gnome-keyring gphoto2 ios mtp nfs
​

finish and enjoy!